description: Nestled in the highly sought-after enclave of Red Rocks, where opportunities are rare and tightly held, this remarkable double-story beach house offers the perfect blend of coastal living and modern convenience. With an easy stroll to the pristine Red Rocks Beach, this is your chance to live the ultimate coastal dream.This family beach house boasts 4 spacious bedrooms, including a master suite with dual access to the upstairs bathroom. Wake up to the soothing sounds of the ocean, step out onto your private balcony, and start your day in paradise.Enjoy the freedom to entertain or relax in style with two separate living areas. The open and airy design provides the perfect space for family gatherings or quiet moments of contemplation. Recently updated, the kitchen features sleek stone benches, a double sink, a 600ml electric oven and cooktop, and a convenient dishwasher. Prepare your favorite meals with ease and style.This property is move-in ready, with new blinds, carpets, and an electric hot water service. Experience the comfort of a home that blends some modern additions with the original features. Stay comfortable year-round with split system heating and cooling units in both living areas. Enjoy the cool sea breeze in summer and cozy warmth in the winter.Step out onto the covered verandah to enjoy the treetop ambience. It's the ideal spot for a morning coffee or simply unwinding with a book and a glass of wine.This property offers both a single garage and a single carport, providing ample space for your vehicles and beach toys. Additional internal storage space is available under the stairs.Situated on an approximately 655 sqm allotment, there's plenty of room to enjoy outdoor activities, create a garden paradise, or simply relish the space and privacy that this property offers. With an easy stroll down to the sheltered north-facing Red Rocks Beach, your days can be filled with sun, sand and beautiful scenery. Additionally, it's just a 5-minute drive to Thompson Avenue and within a short 15-minute drive to popular tourist attractions.Don't miss out on this unique opportunity to make seaside living a reality. Embrace the coastal lifestyle you've always dreamed of. Contact us today to schedule your private viewing of this exceptional Red Rocks Beach retreat.This property for sale in Red Rocks is proudly presented to you by Ray White Real Estate Phillip Island.

description: Alive with period character features that blend with stunning contemporary updates, this magnificent 1920s family home is neatly positioned on a residentially zoned 1237sqm and awaits its new owners.  Highly regarded by many who visit, as the best house in the best street, you will soon appreciate the friendliness of this quiet Yeerongpilly neighbourhood and the position that this property commands.Expansive living areas set over two levels immediately impress. The home encompasses five bedrooms with a sitting room & ensuite in the master suite and a private study within the second bedroom. Three bathrooms fitted with quality tiling, lighting & fixtures will please, as will the formal & informal living areas that include an elegant living room with original fireplace surround positioned off the homes entrance and an expansive downstairs media room. A small separate office is located also on the lower level.The gourmet kitchen fitted with European appliances including Neff induction cook top, healthy option stainless steel steamer & wall oven, Rangehood, Miele dishwasher and Vintec wine fridge is cleverly designed within custom made 2 pac cabinetry. The latest in kitchen culture - black Caesar stone benches & composite granite sink feature with travertine tiled splash backs. This superbly appointed kitchen is ideally positioned in the heart of the home overseeing casual open plan family living & dining that integrate seamlessly via an embankment of French doors to enormous wrap around verandas.  The massive rear deck with built in Bose speakers stretches out to rolling lawns and a fabulous sparkling salt water in ground pool. Those who love to entertain will not be disappointed!All of the contemporary additions have been designed to accentuate space & light in the home and offer a relaxed lifestyle not often available in Queenslander homes. The striking additional living areas blend with the traditional features throughout of archways, breezeways, VJ lined walls, pine flooring, high waist 3 panel doors, casement windows, lead lights & period light fittings. Additional features include ducted air conditioning, insulation, security grills, upgraded wiring & telephone/computer outlets.A 10,000 litre water tank assists with maintaining pool levels, hedges and native gardens within this child and pet friendly fenced rear yard. Plenty of storage can be found throughout the property plus a workshop located off the mud room and bays for double car accommodation.Quality schools, cafes and restaurants are just a short stroll away, and equally well positioned within walking distance to rail, bus and freeway access, Yeronga pool and recreational parkland, Brisbane Golf Club and the new State Tennis Centre at Tennyson Reach.Auction on Site Saturday 14 November at 1pm if not sold before!Proudly presented by:The MARTIN HOOD Teamknown      trusted      provenMartin Hood  0411 220 736Liz Cruse     0422 447 743Direct           3399 8388www.martinhoodteam.com.au

description: Upon entering this beautifully renovated home, you immediately feel the serenity, style and charm this house bestows.  Set in a quiet green leafy locale, it is protected from the harsh Queensland elements and enjoys lovely breezes overlooking a serene undulating vista from the alfresco area towards the rear of the house.  Thanks to its versatile design the lower floor could be used as very comfortably office, a parental retreat or second income source, in essence you are securing two properties here.Positioned just 3kms from the CBD, the Dutton Park locale is in high demand and ever increasing.  Walking distance to West End cafe and dining precincts, South Bank cultural center, cinemas and theatres, your weekends will be spoilt with entertaining choices. There are ample educational choices being in converted Brisbane State High Catchment (the highly anticipated Inner City South Secondary College coming very soon) and Dutton Park Primary School.  It's close to St Laurence's College, Somerville House and St Ita's Primary School and strolling distance over the Green Bridge to the University of Queensland, your children's educational future is set for life.  Please visit Sam Peterffy from Harcourts at your first convenience to secure this stylish and charming abode.  There have been only 6 houses in all of Dutton Park to sell this year, if you are lucky enough to buy this one, you'll understand why residents once they move into this community, don't want to leave.

description: This property has it all - a large, family home comprising 4 bedrooms with two separate living areas, a rumpus room, a pool, ample shedding and nearly 50 acres for your animals to roam. Come and enjoy the tranquil setting. LOCATION:-With the back drop of the Eastern Mount Lofty Ranges and views over the surrounding countryside, you will be amazed that you are only a drive of around 15 minutes to Mannum and the River Murray, Mt Pleasant or Birdwood; 30 minutes to Murray Bridge and the South Eastern Freeway; 45 minutes to Gawler, Mount Barker or the eastern suburbs of Adelaide or just under 60 minutes to Strathalbyn or the Barossa Valley. LAND:- Approx. 18.2ha (44.97acres approx.)  The property is divided into four paddocks and some smaller holding yards. Approximately 16 hectares are divided into two paddocks and are ideal for cropping out for feed or for grazing as they have a gentle undulation and are able to be accessed via the roads. The house paddock is a sheltered, flat area in front of the home and makes an ideal horse arena. Another paddock on the southern side of the home is planted out to Salt Bush. A winter creek traverses the southern corner and is well shaded by mature gums and other trees.The gardens that surround the home include lush lawns and mature Palms to the east, a gravel area around the pool with a magnificent wall of Oleander bushes providing a screen and colour. On the northern side of the home is an irrigation system, which is set on timers, and raised garden beds make gardening a pleasurable experience.  An abundance of fruit trees include dwarf varieties of peach, nectarine, several varieties of citrus, apricots, plums, apples, pear and mulberry. A nature lover’s paradise with several Blue Wrens and other birds making this their home.  RESIDENCE:-The original section of the homestead, which was built in stone in approximately 1895, includes features such as -  pressed tin ceilings, 11 ft high ceilings, jarrah floor boards, ornate fireplaces and sash windows. This home has been lovingly restored and renovated to now include a huge open plan living area with ample windows that allow natural sunlight to flow throughout the home; this area currently comprises the dining area, a casual sitting area and a large family area with a slow combustion heater. The huge, country style kitchen features two cooking areas - a 900mm gas stove and an electric under bench oven and a cook top; whichever your preference you are well catered for. There are cupboards galore and ample working bench space including a moveable work bench with a stone inlay, which is ideal for pastry. The formal lounge room features a pressed tin ceiling and a slow combustion heater and is an ideal area to relax. The sunroom adjoins the lounge and leads out onto the front verandah and lush lawns, which are shaded by two magnificent palms. Two rooms adjacent to the sunroom are currently used as the third bedroom and an office (or fourth bedroom) with BIR. The main passage leads from the kitchen and past the main bedroom, that has a wall of built-ins, to bedroom two, which features a beautiful ceiling rose. These rooms are on the southern side of the home and look out onto the rear verandah, the entertaining area, to the above ground salt water pool and gardens. Normal wet areas include the bathroom, with a vanity, a bath with overhead shower and a toilet, a separate toilet and an extra large laundry with ample cupboard space and even includes the old copper in the corner. An energy efficient home with wide verandahs on all four sides with many windows and doors that, when opened, allow the natural breeze to flow through the home. In addition, there is year round climate control with the assistance of a ducted evaporative cooling system, ceilings fans, and in the cooler months, two slow combustion heaters and gas bayonet points.  A 5.5kW solar system assists with keeping your energy prices down and SA Water is connected to the property. IMPROVEMENTS:-A double carport, adjacent to the double garage, is within close proximity of the home and is alongside the rumpus room, which is fully lined and insulated. Three stables are located within a besser brick building which includes a tack room, feed room and an area that had been used for milking goats and cows - with the original head bails still in place. A concrete area in front of the stables is an ideal wash down or prep area as it is undercover and a rain water tank is just around the corner. A large besser brick implement shed with a concrete floor is adjacent to this area. A small holding paddock with yards and a cattle crush and ramp is adjacent to the main entrance gate. Wood shed, chook pen and a dog run. SUMMARY:-An ideal lifestyle property that has the charm of yesteryear but has all the modern creature comforts that one expects. Room for your family and beloved animals. Come and enjoy the peaceful and tranquil setting.

description: Are you looking for that property with something extra? Well, this home is for you. Set on approximately 29.3 acres in the increasingly popular Shelbourne area, the property sprawls from Foreman Road with the boundary at the back of the property being Spring Creek. Perfect for horses or hobby livestock, there are two paddocks of around one acre each bordering Foreman Road with one comprising a horse shelter. The back paddocks have a large dam and there is loads of character with the outskirts of the property comprising trees and sandy creek beds.This unique residence works in two ways and could provide a dual living component for extended family or growing teenagers, Airbnb or just enjoy it yourself. The main home is approximately 20 squares under roof; this has been freshly painted with new flooring, a well maintained modern kitchen and a flow that sees the master bedroom at one end of the home with a large walk-through robe and updated ensuite. The hub of the home with the dining, main lounge and smaller living room are all linked within a semi open plan, with the focal point being a solid fuel heater. Towards the other end of the home are a further three bedrooms, all with built-in robes and they are serviced by a good sized main bathroom (virtual 3D tour can be viewed on this listing). The dining room steps down outside to a covered outdoor area in excess of 100 square metres that takes advantage of the views on offer and provides a perfect entertainment area complete with a fully decked out BBQ kitchen and pizza oven. Overlooking the yard at a right angle to the entertainment area is the second space measuring 21.5 x 8 metres with two thirds of this area being fully lined, air conditioned and offering up a huge living space complete with polished concrete floors, a wall mounted TV and currently it serves the purpose of a pool table area. Overlooking this is a food prep area with running water and sink plus a fridge space. Also attached is a storage or study space plus a wet room with toilet. The other part of the structure has a concrete floor and is accessed separately through a roller door.Other features for this property include;- 6 kW solar panels and double carport- 9 x 6 metre powered shed and garden shed - Enclosed chook run and separate veggie patch - Fruit trees bordering the main area- 4 poly tanks - 15,000 gallons of water and 2 meg catchment damThere is so much more on offer with this property so you are invited to contact listing agent Nathan Diss to explore this wonderful property.

description: Blessed with a rare cliff-top position and mesmerising 180 degree bay vistas from the tip of the Peninsula to the twinkling lights of the Melbourne city skyline; this sumptuous 4 bedroom plus study family home is certain to impress the most fastidious buyer.'Angliss House' was originally commissioned and built for Sir William Angliss of national pastoral acclaim and has been tastefully renovated and extended to provide a luxurious fusion of classical and modern architecture.The property is privately set in serene gardens of 2,958sqm approx. and discretely introduced via a remote gateway ahead of a long meandering sealed drive amongst prolific gardens, lush lawns culminating into a substantial forecourt with water feature flanked by the main house and separate garaging opposite.Enter inside to realise the soaring ceilings of the large gallery foyer, the instant bay views and an abundance of natural light courtesy of the ideal north-westerly orientation. Explore the fluid layout of the entry level where a series of large reception rooms merge seamlessly designed around harnessing the sparkling aspect of the water at every angle.On the right of the entry discover a sizeable lounge come dining space with marble tiling, bespoke cabinetry, oversized floor to ceiling windows and electric glass door for instant access to the great outdoors, not to forget a cosy electric heater adding to the memorable ambiance of this space.Opposite features the hub of the home dedicated to a large open plan marble gourmet kitchen with premium Miele appliances such as integrated steam oven, dual electric ovens, dishwasher, espresso machine and two Bosch induction cook-tops easily catering to requisite soirées of any size. The kitchen also incorporates generous custom cabinetry with large pantry, breakfast bar and wine fridge storage.Adjacently the enormous family room and meals area with rich timber parquetry flooring measures nearly 60sqm and provides further luxuriant living spaces and direct access to the poolside alfresco terrace and the Balinese enthused gazebo offering yet another zone for elegant entertaining and more of those breathtaking views abound.The first floor comprises of four double bedrooms (most with views) fitted with plush carpet, built-in or walk-in robes and serviced by a decadent fully tiled family bathroom with stone vanity, large shower, deep-soaking bath and separate WC. The third bedroom has its own en-suite as does the lavish master bedroom with retreat, his and her walk-in robe and en-suite featuring twin vanity, glazed shower room with views of the water and separate WC for the fortunate inhabitants of this blissful part of the home.Also on this level; a refined home-office and superbly proportioned second living room appointed with tailored-made wall cabinetry and immediate admission to the large covered balcony with the big blue for an inspiring backdrop.Savour this unique opportunity to secure a magnificent expansive home in a tightly held dress circle position mere moments to the beach below, excellent schools and the vibrancy of Mount Eliza village a short drive away.INSPECT NOW TO REALISE!Further inclusions; Gas hydronic heating & evaporative cooling throughout, 5kW solar panel system, solar heated fully tiled wet-edge swimming pool, unforgettable bay views with poolside alfresco terrace & enclosed gazebo with glass concertina doors, separate 3-4 auto garage & carport / workshop, remote gateway, intercom, large undercover balcony, gourmet kitchen, multitude of dynamic living spaces over two levels, mature gardens & verdant lush lawns, water tank, irrigation, NBN and much more..

description: Sold by Matthew Pillios, Kay & Burton Celebrating its prized Dendy Park precinct locale, an impeccably curated aesthetic fit-out, complemented by uncompromised attention to detail and resort-style alfresco amenities has effortlessly elevated the luxury and liveability of this as-new, 5-bedroom contemporary family entertainer.Privately and securely set behind a high wall, with automated gates and video intercom entry, the custom-crafted double-storey home impresses from the get-go with an oversized timber-batten door opening to reveal a generously proportioned entry foyer elegantly floored with Engineered Oak and illuminated by Articolo sconce lighting and centred with an American oak open staircase. Living and leisure amenities abound with flowing formal and informal living spaces on both levels, a 'gold-class' equipped home cinema, an upper-level built-in wet bar, and an elegant study/home office, to more than adequately support the five bedrooms, four luxe bathrooms and two powder rooms. Sleek, handle-free timber-veneered and matt 2-pac joinery throughout is both beautiful and practical, while expanses of majestic natural stone and marble, sweep across bench and countertops.The showstopping kitchen features a curved Super White stone island bench/breakfast bar, and exquisite matt black cabinetry custom-crafted to showcase or conceal displayed and integrated Gaggenau and Liebherr appliances including a wine fridge, fridge/freezer, double ovens, induction cooktop and dishwasher, while the equally impressive adjoining butlers' kitchen and pantry has a Gaggenau gas cooktop.Floor-to-ceiling sliding glass connects to the undercover alfresco zone, with gas-plumbed barbecue, built-in fridge and integrated sound-system speakers, and the resort-like fully tiled solar-heated swimming pool is edged with a stacked stone effect dwarf-wall.The pristine double garage with workshop/storage area has a remote auto door, plus a rear access roller door, and internal access door, and is set behind secure off-street parking for an additional two vehicles.Additional luxuries include choice of two master suites on either level, three bathrooms with free-standing Meek bathware tubs, Signorina and Artedomus tiling, high-end tapware, a lavish north-facing upper-level master suite with automated blinds and external awnings, sumptuous pure wool carpets, Escea fireplace, designer lighting, zoned central heating and cooling, stone laundry with external access, rooftop solar panels and an automated watering system. The home cinema is fitted with an Epson 4k projector, 120 inch screen, Yamaha receive, and integrated speakers. Ideal beachside location with the wide-open spaces of Dendy Park and Brighton Golf Course just steps away, along with local cafes and restaurants, and close to some of Brighton's leading schools including St. Leonards College and Haileybury College.

description: Nestled in the highly sought-after area of Burpengary East, this exceptional display home combines contemporary design with high-end finishes, providing the ultimate living experience. Set on a generous 408m² block, this home offers spacious, functional areas that cater to the needs of modern families. Every detail has been carefully considered, ensuring comfort, convenience, and style in every corner.The heart of the home is the expansive kitchen, which boasts 40mm stone edge benchtops with waterfall ends, 900mm appliances with an integrated rangehood, and a stunning herringbone splashback. The shaker-style cabinetry and luxurious butler's pantry, featuring a white Oliveri sink, are perfect for those who love to entertain. The adjacent living areas are designed with hybrid timber-look flooring, offering both durability and appeal.This home has been thoughtfully designed for year-round comfort, with a Daikin Ducted 6-Zone air-conditioning system featuring MyAir technology. High 9ft ceilings throughout contribute to a light, airy ambiance, while the luxurious bathrooms feature rain showerheads and a freestanding bathtub for the ultimate in relaxation. description: The majority of houses/units in Redwood Village are around the 12-16 squares in size.  This house is approximately 25 squares in size, which is almost double the size of anything else in this quiet over 50s village, but not double the price. Realistically priced is this three bedroom two bathroom home that has a huge lounge room, a very sizeable dining room and a sunroom, which can be accessed both internally and from the garden. Beautiful Mountain views can be enjoyed from the front three rooms. This home has two master bedrooms, complete with their own en-suite bathrooms and large built in wardrobes. The third bedroom or study has a built-in Blackwood shelving over the entire wall. This would be perfect for a study or to show off your treasures.The huge lounge room has a custom made Tasmanian oak, glass door cabinet with full-length hinges, already in place, but believe me you will still have room for all of your precious furniture and bits and pieces.  Unusually this entire house and property has not one step in sight, with no fences to maintain, it has underground power, a ducted vacuum system and has NBN installed.There is a valuable rock wall at the rear, and the garden soil is excellent for growing fruit trees.  There is a particularly abundant Moor Park apricot tree in the front garden. This home has insulation in the ceiling, and has excellent and efficient heating and a drying cupboard in the laundry.Entry is either off Village Drive or park in the oversized double carport with ample space to reverse your vehicle and drive out front ways and with extra off street car parking.  This would be great for the extended family when they are visiting.There is a new electrical switchboard that has been installed by a master electrician. There is nothing to do as everything has been very well maintained over the past ten years with one fastidious owner.The Body Corporate fee is only $25 per month and this includes insurance on the common ground and the insurance on the external part of your house.This house is conveniently located within walking distance to shopping, services and public transport.

description: This property is under contract: A rare opportunity has arisen to secure this impressive, single level, waterfront residence in the highly sought after Benowa Waters.  Quietly nestled at the end of a cul-de-sac and boasting a low maintenance,  1056sqm fully fenced block, there is  plenty of room for the kids to play, the jetski/trailer to be stored (excellent side access) and the family to relax by the pool while enjoying the wide water  and hinterland views.  There is also plenty of space inside, with 4 bedrooms, multiple living areas, 3 bathrooms and a 3 bay garage converted into living space.Entering the property you will immediately be impressed by the spectacular water views.  The thoughtful design takes advantage of the 15.5 meters of water frontage, with every room maximising its view, while enjoying a light and airy feel.Elegantly simple, the open plan lounge / dining seamlessly integrates with the outdoor deck adding to the feeling of space and openness.  The deck is the ideal spot for casual alfresco dining, or sinking into a comfortable lounge with your favorite book, while (of course) also enjoying spectacular views of the lake and hinterland. Designed to suit all occasions from entertaining guests to relaxing after a day at work, this spacious, family home is sure to impress the most discerning buyer.Features include:Ergonomically designed gourmet kitchen with stone bench-tops & gas cooking.Travertine tiles and timber flooring.Brand new split-system air-conditioners in every room.Spacious open plan living areas.High ceilings - creating a relaxed feeling of open space.4 bedrooms.3 Bathrooms.Two ensuited bedrooms (master with spa)Fabulous patio overlooking wide lake & mountain views.Sparkling lap pool.Low maintenance gardens. Fully fenced with remote controlled security gate.Built-in intercom plus alarm system. Three Bay garage, cleverly converted as living space with air conditioningSide access perfect for storing and JetSki or trailer. Crimsafe security Enjoy the famous Gold Coast lifestyle, in one of the most sought after waterfront addresses.Walking distance to:Benowa High & Primary SchoolSt Kevins Primary SchoolBenowa Gardens shopping centrePindara HospitalBotanical Gardens & Dog Off Leash AreaBenowa/Benowa Waters is home of the Gold Coast City’s Regional Botanic Gardens which consists of 31 spectacular hectares with parks, natural billabongs, children's playground, BBQ’s & dog off leash areas.Benowa/Benowa Waters is highly prized for its central location and proximity to Surfers Paradise. Bordered mostly by waterways including Main River, Benowa is located to the west of the Isle of Capri and Bundall, and is just five kilometres from the beach.A popular choice with families and couples, Benowa's services include the Benowa Gardens Shopping Centre, Pindara Private Hospital, the Royal Pines Resort Golf Course and three schools (public and private).
